                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1212: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-05T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 5, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>327. Your 851, September 30, 6 p.m.,<note n="94" xml:id="d552fn94">Not
                        printed.</note> and Department’s 313, September 20, 7 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>After carefully considering the procedure described in your paragraphs 1
                        and 2 and the comments contained in your paragraph 4 the Department is
                        convinced that serious difficulties may in practice arise if there be
                        authorized any alternative so far proposed to the requirement laid down in
                        the Department’s telegram 139, of April 27, 2 p.m., paragraph 2.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Reverting therefore to that requirement, you are requested to inform
                        persons interested that as a condition precedent to the issuing of a license
                        for the exportation of arms to China the Department will require that there
                        be presented by the Chinese diplomatic representative at Washington a
                        request on the part of his Government that the American Government authorize
                        exportation.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
